The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, April 3: Growth of six key infrastructure sectors accelerated to 8.7 per cent in February 2008, reviving hopes that industrial production will speed up and arrest an economic slowdown. Growth in coal, power and cement, three of the six industries that make up the core sector, aided the healthy growth in February compared with 7.6 per cent a year ago. However, in April-February 2007-08 period, infrastructure growth remained lower at 5.6 per cent compared with 8.7 per cent a year ago because of less than five per cent growth in the four preceding months this fiscal.                             
	 New Delhi, April 3: Bharti Airtel, Vodafone Essar and Idea Cellular have been served notice of enquiry by the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Commission for allegedly forming a cartel to distort competition.                            
	 London, April 3: Tesco has identified a preferred partner to enter the Indian retail market through the back door, a Daily Mail report said. The partner is likely to be among a group that includes Mahindra and Mahindra, Bombay Dyeing and the National Dairy Development Board.                            
	 New Delhi, April 3: Tata Motors has received the Thailand governments approval to set up a facility to manufacture eco cars at an estimated investment of Rs 760-1,015 crore.                            
	 Mumbai, April 3:The RBI has eased the overseas investment limit for mutual funds to $7 billion from $5 billion with immediate effect.
                                                                                                                                 
